---
import Layout from "@layouts/Layout.astro";

import Glupdates from "@components/Glupdates.astro";

const title = "Gelsey Land";
const subtitle = "welcome to park services";
const bannerImage = "/bg/sayworldbg.webp";
const tinyImage = "/smalls/sm-balloons.gif";
---

<head>
	<meta
		http-equiv="Content-Security-Policy"
		content="connect-src 'self' data: blob: https://status.cafe;"
	/>
</head>

<Layout
	title={title}
	subtitle={subtitle}
	bannerImage={bannerImage}
	tinyImage={tinyImage}
>
	<div slot="after-navl"></div>
	<div slot="main-text">
		<div class="flexbox">
			<p>
				thank you for visiting the internets first themepark ran by a
				little clown man! enjoy the rides, download our pixels
				(ethically sourced of course), and fly to places inside my
				imagination. Here you'll find collections dedicated to the
				fantasies born of music, movies, games, and more. We have more
				media recommendations than you can possibly spend your dwindling
				free time with. So buckle up, hold on to your cotton candy, and
				prepare for a whimsical journey through the colorful world of
				Gelsey Land! &#127913;
			</p>
			<div><img src="/images/littleman.webp" /></div>
		</div>
		<div class="divider-balloon"></div>
		<h3>Apr 2026 to do</h3>
		<ul>
			<li>
				<s>create a landing page</s></li>
				<li><s>separate my style css and my build css</s></li>
			</li>
		</ul>
		</div>
		<div slot="after-navr"></div>

		<div slot="full">
			<h1>mission statement</h1>
			<p>
				This site is more than just a cutesy theme for a personal site
				... okay tbf that is a large part of it but that's not the only
				reason. Everyday I experience like 2 million various stimuli:
				the song on my alarm, the first article I read on my feed, the
				video I play in the background as I grind on my mobage while
				simultaneously working on a project. I live and walk through
				noise and clutter. My theme park is where I make sense of
				everything. I freeze the moments and take in the little details.
				Its funny to think of a big crazy loud theme park as a place for
				quiet contemplation, but I never have liked traditional
				meditating or Thoreau style writers retreats. My brain is loud
				and exciting. I dont want to clear my head i just want to be
				able to sit in the passengers seat and experience my own
				thoughts as a guest. I hope you enjoy the ride. &#127906;
			</p>
			<img src="/div/bluepinkdiv.png" />
		</div>

		<div slot="left-half">
			<section class="half">
				<Glupdates />
			</section>
		</div>
		<div slot="right-half">
			<section class="half">
				<form method="post" action="https://poll.pollcode.com/65663779"><div style="padding:2px 0px 4px 2px;"><strong>What kinda blog posts would you like to see?</strong></div><input type="radio" name="answer" value="1" id="answer656637791" style="float:left;" /><label for="answer656637791" style="float:left;width:150px;">Free Media/Web Tuts</label><div style="clear:both;height:2px;"></div><input type="radio" name="answer" value="2" id="answer656637792" style="float:left;" /><label for="answer656637792" style="float:left;width:150px;">Idol Group Deep Dives</label><div style="clear:both;height:2px;"></div><input type="radio" name="answer" value="3" id="answer656637793" style="float:left;" /><label for="answer656637793" style="float:left;width:150px;">Infinity Nikki stuff</label><div style="clear:both;height:2px;"></div><input type="radio" name="answer" value="4" id="answer656637794" style="float:left;" /><label for="answer656637794" style="float:left;width:150px;">One Piece Arc Meditations</label><div style="clear:both;height:2px;"></div><input type="radio" name="answer" value="5" id="answer656637795" style="float:left;" /><label for="answer656637795" style="float:left;width:150px;">Sticker Sheets/Pixel Freebies</label><div style="clear:both;height:2px;"></div><input type="radio" name="answer" value="6" id="answer656637796" style="float:left;" /><label for="answer656637796" style="float:left;width:150px;">Horror Movie Recaps</label><div style="clear:both;height:2px;"></div><input type="radio" name="answer" value="7" id="answer656637797" style="float:left;" /><label for="answer656637797" style="float:left;width:150px;">Otome Reviews</label><div style="clear:both;height:2px;"></div><input type="radio" name="answer" value="8" id="answer656637798" style="float:left;" /><label for="answer656637798" style="float:left;width:150px;">Life Advice/Routines for neurospiced folk</label><div style="clear:both;height:2px;"></div><input type="radio" name="answer" value="9" id="answer656637799" style="float:left;" /><label for="answer656637799" style="float:left;width:150px;">other ?????????</label><div style="clear:both;height:2px;"></div><div align="center" style="padding:3px;"><input type="submit" value=" Vote ">&nbsp;<input type="submit" name="view" value=" View "></div><div align="right" style="font-size:10px">pollcode.com <a href="https://pollcode.com/">free polls</a></div></div></form>
			</section>
		</div>
	</div>
	<style>
		.hero {
			background:
				url("/tables/buntingframe.png"), url("/umpd/groupphoto.png");
			background-size: cover, cover;
			background-position: center, center;
			background-repeat: no-repeat, no-repeat;
			height: 10rem;
			position: relative;
		}
		.hero a {
			margin: 0;
			position: absolute;
			top: 50%;
			left: 50%;
			-ms-transform: translate(-50%, -50%);
			transform: translate(-50%, -50%);
			font-size: 1rem !important ;
		}
	</style>
</Layout>
